==English==
===Etymology===
From Old French ''solas'', from Latin ''[[solatium]]'', from ''[[solari]]'' "console"

===Noun===
'''solace'''
#[[Comfort]] or [[consolation]] in a time of [[distress]].
#A source of comfort or consolation.

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[troost]]
*Finnish: [[lohtu]]

====Synonyms====
*[[comfort]]
*[[consolation]]
*[[relief]]
*[[support]]

====Derived terms====
*[[solaceful]]
*[[solacement]]

===Verb===
'''to solace'''
# Give solace to; [[comfort]]; [[cheer]]; [[console]].
#[[Allay]] or [[assuage]].

====Translations====
